{
    "audio_file": "E:\\Podcast-Analyser\\automated-podcast-transcription\\backend\\uploads\\1767442864775.mp3",
    "language": "en",
    "segments": [
        {
            "start": 0.0,
            "end": 1.6400000000000001,
            "text": " DREAMS"
        },
        {
            "start": 1.6600000000000001,
            "end": 2.66,
            "text": " DREAMS"
        },
        {
            "start": 2.68,
            "end": 4.68,
            "text": " DREAMS"
        },
        {
            "start": 4.7,
            "end": 6.7,
            "text": " DREAMS"
        },
        {
            "start": 6.72,
            "end": 8.22,
            "text": " DREAMS"
        },
        {
            "start": 12.76,
            "end": 18.740000000000002,
            "text": " In the mid-90s, the CDC and Kaiser Permanente discovered an exposure"
        },
        {
            "start": 18.76,
            "end": 23.400000000000002,
            "text": " that dramatically increased the risk for seven out of ten"
        },
        {
            "start": 23.42,
            "end": 27.060000000000002,
            "text": " of the leading causes of death in the United States."
        },
        {
            "start": 27.12,
            "end": 30.64,
            "text": " In high doses, it affects brain development,"
        },
        {
            "start": 30.660000000000004,
            "end": 34.120000000000005,
            "text": " the immune system, hormonal systems,"
        },
        {
            "start": 34.14,
            "end": 38.1,
            "text": " and even the way our DNA is read and transcribed."
        },
        {
            "start": 38.88,
            "end": 42.08,
            "text": " Folks who are exposed in very high doses"
        },
        {
            "start": 42.1,
            "end": 46.540000000000006,
            "text": " have tripled the lifetime risk of heart disease and lung cancer"
        },
        {
            "start": 46.56,
            "end": 50.84,
            "text": " and a 20-year difference in life expectancy."
        },
        {
            "start": 51.78,
            "end": 57.18000000000001,
            "text": " And yet doctors today are not trained in routine screening or treatment."
        },
        {
            "start": 58.1,
            "end": 63.78,
            "text": " Now, the exposure I'm talking about is not a pesticide or a packaging chemical."
        },
        {
            "start": 63.800000000000004,
            "end": 65.68,
            "text": " It's childhood trauma."
        },
        {
            "start": 67.08000000000001,
            "end": 69.56,
            "text": " Okay, what kind of trauma am I talking about here?"
        },
        {
            "start": 69.58000000000001,
            "end": 73.96000000000001,
            "text": " I'm not talking about failing a test or losing a basketball game."
        },
        {
            "start": 73.98,
            "end": 78.5,
            "text": " I am talking about threats that are so severe or pervasive"
        },
        {
            "start": 78.52,
            "end": 83.14,
            "text": " that they literally get under our skin and change our physiology,"
        },
        {
            "start": 83.16,
            "end": 87.34,
            "text": " things like abuse or neglect or growing up with a parent"
        },
        {
            "start": 87.36,
            "end": 90.88,
            "text": " who struggles with mental illness or substance dependence."
        },
        {
            "start": 91.92,
            "end": 93.48,
            "text": " Now, for a long time,"
        },
        {
            "start": 93.5,
            "end": 96.6,
            "text": " I viewed these things in the way I was trained to view them,"
        },
        {
            "start": 96.62,
            "end": 100.64,
            "text": " either as a social problem referred to social services"
        },
        {
            "start": 100.66,
            "end": 104.76,
            "text": " or as a mental health problem referred to mental health services."
        },
        {
            "start": 105.76,
            "end": 110.62,
            "text": " And then something happened to make me rethink my entire approach."
        },
        {
            "start": 111.76,
            "end": 113.30000000000001,
            "text": " When I finished my residency,"
        },
        {
            "start": 113.32000000000001,
            "end": 116.94,
            "text": " I wanted to go someplace where I felt really needed,"
        },
        {
            "start": 116.96000000000001,
            "end": 120.06,
            "text": " someplace where I could make a difference."
        },
        {
            "start": 120.08000000000001,
            "end": 123.5,
            "text": " So I came to work for California Pacific Medical Center,"
        },
        {
            "start": 123.52000000000001,
            "end": 127.48,
            "text": " one of the best private hospitals in Northern California,"
        },
        {
            "start": 127.5,
            "end": 131.54000000000002,
            "text": " and together, we opened a clinic in Bayview Hunters Point,"
        },
        {
            "start": 131.66,
            "end": 136.34,
            "text": " one of the poorest, most underserved neighborhoods in San Francisco."
        },
        {
            "start": 136.35999999999999,
            "end": 138.16,
            "text": " Now, prior to that point,"
        },
        {
            "start": 138.18,
            "end": 141.12,
            "text": " there had been only one pediatrician in all of Bayview"
        },
        {
            "start": 141.14,
            "end": 144.45999999999998,
            "text": " to serve more than 10,000 children."
        },
        {
            "start": 144.48,
            "end": 146.06,
            "text": " So we hung a shingle"
        },
        {
            "start": 146.07999999999998,
            "end": 149.16,
            "text": " and we were able to provide top-quality care,"
        },
        {
            "start": 149.18,
            "end": 151.34,
            "text": " regardless of ability to pay."
        },
        {
            "start": 151.35999999999999,
            "end": 152.84,
            "text": " It was so cool."
        },
        {
            "start": 152.85999999999999,
            "end": 155.44,
            "text": " We targeted the typical health disparities,"
        },
        {
            "start": 155.45999999999998,
            "end": 160.32,
            "text": " access to care, immunization rates, asthma hospitalization rates,"
        },
        {
            "start": 160.34,
            "end": 162.26,
            "text": " and we hit all of our numbers."
        },
        {
            "start": 162.28,
            "end": 164.28,
            "text": " We felt very proud of ourselves."
        },
        {
            "start": 165.51999999999998,
            "end": 168.66,
            "text": " But then I started noticing a disturbing trend."
        },
        {
            "start": 168.68,
            "end": 172.22,
            "text": " A lot of kids were being referred to me for ADHD,"
        },
        {
            "start": 172.23999999999998,
            "end": 175.6,
            "text": " or attention deficit hyperactivity disorder."
        },
        {
            "start": 175.62,
            "end": 180.62,
            "text": " But when I actually did a thorough history and physical,"
        },
        {
            "start": 180.64,
            "end": 183.57999999999998,
            "text": " what I found was that for most of my patients,"
        },
        {
            "start": 183.6,
            "end": 187.18,
            "text": " I couldn't make a diagnosis of ADHD."
        },
        {
            "start": 187.20000000000002,
            "end": 192.52,
            "text": " Most of the kids I was seeing had experienced such severe trauma"
        },
        {
            "start": 192.54000000000002,
            "end": 196.0,
            "text": " that it felt like something else was going on."
        },
        {
            "start": 196.02,
            "end": 200.1,
            "text": " Somehow, I was missing something important."
        },
        {
            "start": 201.62,
            "end": 205.44,
            "text": " Now, before I did my residency, I did a master's degree in public health."
        },
        {
            "start": 205.46,
            "end": 208.38,
            "text": " And one of the things that they teach you in public health school"
        },
        {
            "start": 208.4,
            "end": 209.94,
            "text": " is that if you're a doctor"
        },
        {
            "start": 209.96,
            "end": 213.82,
            "text": " and you see 100 kids that all drink from the same well"
        },
        {
            "start": 213.88,
            "end": 217.51999999999998,
            "text": " and 98 of them develop diarrhea,"
        },
        {
            "start": 217.54,
            "end": 219.72,
            "text": " you can go ahead and write that prescription"
        },
        {
            "start": 219.73999999999998,
            "end": 224.14,
            "text": " for dose after dose after dose of antibiotics,"
        },
        {
            "start": 224.16,
            "end": 226.79999999999998,
            "text": " or you can walk over and say,"
        },
        {
            "start": 226.82,
            "end": 229.66,
            "text": " what the hell is in this well?"
        },
        {
            "start": 229.68,
            "end": 233.76,
            "text": " So I began reading everything that I could get my hands on"
        },
        {
            "start": 233.78,
            "end": 236.45999999999998,
            "text": " about how exposure to adversity"
        },
        {
            "start": 236.48,
            "end": 240.07999999999998,
            "text": " affects the developing brains and bodies of children."
        },
        {
            "start": 240.08,
            "end": 243.78,
            "text": " And then one day, my colleague walked into my office"
        },
        {
            "start": 243.8,
            "end": 245.06,
            "text": " and he said,"
        },
        {
            "start": 245.08,
            "end": 247.60000000000002,
            "text": " Dr. Burke, have you seen this?"
        },
        {
            "start": 248.9,
            "end": 252.86,
            "text": " In his hand was a copy of a research study"
        },
        {
            "start": 252.88000000000002,
            "end": 255.8,
            "text": " called the Adverse Childhood Experiences Study."
        },
        {
            "start": 256.54,
            "end": 260.56,
            "text": " That day changed my clinical practice"
        },
        {
            "start": 260.58000000000004,
            "end": 263.12,
            "text": " and ultimately my career."
        },
        {
            "start": 264.18,
            "end": 266.62,
            "text": " The Adverse Childhood Experiences Study"
        },
        {
            "start": 266.64,
            "end": 269.54,
            "text": " is something that everybody needs to know about."
        },
        {
            "start": 269.56,
            "end": 272.44,
            "text": " It was done by Dr. Vince Feliti at Kaiser"
        },
        {
            "start": 272.46000000000004,
            "end": 274.68,
            "text": " and Dr. Bob Onda at the CDC."
        },
        {
            "start": 274.70000000000005,
            "end": 280.96000000000004,
            "text": " And together, they asked 17 and a half thousand adults"
        },
        {
            "start": 280.98,
            "end": 283.28000000000003,
            "text": " about their history of exposure"
        },
        {
            "start": 283.3,
            "end": 287.88,
            "text": " to what they called Adverse Childhood Experiences, or ACEs."
        },
        {
            "start": 288.84000000000003,
            "end": 292.58000000000004,
            "text": " Those include physical, emotional, or sexual abuse,"
        },
        {
            "start": 292.6,
            "end": 296.82000000000005,
            "text": " physical or emotional neglect, parental mental illness,"
        },
        {
            "start": 296.84,
            "end": 300.04,
            "text": " substance dependence, incarceration,"
        },
        {
            "start": 300.06,
            "end": 302.52,
            "text": " parental separation or divorce,"
        },
        {
            "start": 302.54,
            "end": 304.96,
            "text": " or domestic violence."
        },
        {
            "start": 304.98,
            "end": 308.76,
            "text": " For every yes, you would get a point on your ACE score."
        },
        {
            "start": 309.6,
            "end": 313.56,
            "text": " And then what they did was they correlated these ACE scores"
        },
        {
            "start": 313.58,
            "end": 315.9,
            "text": " against health outcomes."
        },
        {
            "start": 317.03999999999996,
            "end": 320.08,
            "text": " What they found was striking."
        },
        {
            "start": 320.1,
            "end": 320.9,
            "text": " Two things."
        },
        {
            "start": 320.92,
            "end": 322.4,
            "text": " Number one,"
        },
        {
            "start": 322.42,
            "end": 325.38,
            "text": " ACEs are incredibly common."
        },
        {
            "start": 325.42,
            "end": 329.88,
            "text": " Sixty-seven percent of the population"
        },
        {
            "start": 329.9,
            "end": 332.1,
            "text": " had at least one ACE."
        },
        {
            "start": 332.12,
            "end": 335.24,
            "text": " And 12.6 percent, one in eight,"
        },
        {
            "start": 335.26,
            "end": 337.9,
            "text": " had four or more ACEs."
        },
        {
            "start": 338.78,
            "end": 340.74,
            "text": " The second thing that they found"
        },
        {
            "start": 340.76,
            "end": 344.65999999999997,
            "text": " was that there was a dose-response relationship"
        },
        {
            "start": 344.68,
            "end": 347.98,
            "text": " between ACEs and health outcomes."
        },
        {
            "start": 349.14,
            "end": 352.94,
            "text": " The higher your ACE score, the worse your health outcomes."
        },
        {
            "start": 352.94,
            "end": 355.92,
            "text": " For a person with an ACE score of four or more,"
        },
        {
            "start": 355.94,
            "end": 359.9,
            "text": " their relative risk of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease"
        },
        {
            "start": 359.92,
            "end": 364.92,
            "text": " was two and a half times that of someone with an ACE score of zero."
        },
        {
            "start": 364.94,
            "end": 368.18,
            "text": " For hepatitis, it was also two and a half times."
        },
        {
            "start": 368.2,
            "end": 371.38,
            "text": " For depression, it was four and a half times."
        },
        {
            "start": 371.4,
            "end": 375.64,
            "text": " For suicidality, it was 12 times."
        },
        {
            "start": 375.65999999999997,
            "end": 378.76,
            "text": " A person with an ACE score of seven or more"
        },
        {
            "start": 378.78,
            "end": 382.74,
            "text": " had triple the lifetime risk of lung cancer"
        },
        {
            "start": 382.74,
            "end": 386.64,
            "text": " and three and a half times the risk of ischemic heart disease,"
        },
        {
            "start": 386.66,
            "end": 389.74,
            "text": " the number one killer in the United States of America."
        },
        {
            "start": 391.06,
            "end": 393.6,
            "text": " Well, of course, this makes sense."
        },
        {
            "start": 393.62,
            "end": 397.38,
            "text": " You know, some people looked at this data and they said,"
        },
        {
            "start": 397.40000000000003,
            "end": 401.1,
            "text": " come on, you know, you have a rough childhood,"
        },
        {
            "start": 401.12,
            "end": 403.78000000000003,
            "text": " you're more likely to drink and smoke"
        },
        {
            "start": 403.8,
            "end": 406.24,
            "text": " and do all these things that are going to ruin your health."
        },
        {
            "start": 406.26,
            "end": 407.74,
            "text": " This isn't science."
        },
        {
            "start": 407.76,
            "end": 409.48,
            "text": " This is just bad behavior."
        },
        {
            "start": 410.48,
            "end": 414.48,
            "text": " It turns out this is exactly where the science comes in."
        },
        {
            "start": 415.48,
            "end": 419.12,
            "text": " We now understand better than we ever have before"
        },
        {
            "start": 420.24,
            "end": 423.12,
            "text": " how exposure to early adversity"
        },
        {
            "start": 423.14000000000004,
            "end": 426.26,
            "text": " affects the developing brains and bodies of children."
        },
        {
            "start": 426.28000000000003,
            "end": 429.12,
            "text": " It affects areas like the nucleus accumbens,"
        },
        {
            "start": 429.14000000000004,
            "end": 431.74,
            "text": " the pleasure and reward center of the brain"
        },
        {
            "start": 431.76,
            "end": 434.58000000000004,
            "text": " that is implicated in substance dependence."
        },
        {
            "start": 434.6,
            "end": 437.38,
            "text": " It inhibits the prefrontal cortex,"
        },
        {
            "start": 437.62,
            "end": 441.12,
            "text": " which is necessary for impulse control and executive function,"
        },
        {
            "start": 441.14,
            "end": 443.38,
            "text": " a critical area for learning."
        },
        {
            "start": 443.4,
            "end": 445.28,
            "text": " And on MRI scans,"
        },
        {
            "start": 445.3,
            "end": 449.28,
            "text": " we see measurable differences in the amygdala,"
        },
        {
            "start": 449.3,
            "end": 451.28,
            "text": " the brain's fear response center."
        },
        {
            "start": 452.14,
            "end": 455.64,
            "text": " So there are real neurologic reasons"
        },
        {
            "start": 455.65999999999997,
            "end": 459.14,
            "text": " why folks exposed to high doses of adversity"
        },
        {
            "start": 459.15999999999997,
            "end": 462.32,
            "text": " are more likely to engage in high-risk behavior,"
        },
        {
            "start": 462.34,
            "end": 464.36,
            "text": " and that's important to know."
        },
        {
            "start": 464.38,
            "end": 467.84000000000003,
            "text": " But it turns out that even if you don't engage"
        },
        {
            "start": 467.86,
            "end": 469.86,
            "text": " in any high-risk behavior,"
        },
        {
            "start": 469.88,
            "end": 474.98,
            "text": " you're still more likely to develop heart disease or cancer."
        },
        {
            "start": 476.12,
            "end": 482.06,
            "text": " The reason for this has to do with the hypothalamic pituitary adrenal axis,"
        },
        {
            "start": 482.08000000000004,
            "end": 485.74,
            "text": " the brain's and body's stress response system"
        },
        {
            "start": 485.76,
            "end": 489.48,
            "text": " that governs our fight-or-flight response."
        },
        {
            "start": 489.5,
            "end": 491.2,
            "text": " How does it work?"
        },
        {
            "start": 491.2,
            "end": 494.88,
            "text": " Well, imagine you're walking in the forest and you see a bear."
        },
        {
            "start": 494.9,
            "end": 499.12,
            "text": " Immediately, your hypothalamus sends a signal to your pituitary,"
        },
        {
            "start": 499.14,
            "end": 501.32,
            "text": " it sends a signal to your adrenal gland"
        },
        {
            "start": 501.34,
            "end": 504.86,
            "text": " that says, release stress hormones, adrenaline, cortisol."
        },
        {
            "start": 505.53999999999996,
            "end": 507.68,
            "text": " And so your heart starts to pound,"
        },
        {
            "start": 507.7,
            "end": 510.41999999999996,
            "text": " your pupils dilate, your airways open up,"
        },
        {
            "start": 510.44,
            "end": 514.64,
            "text": " and you are ready to either fight that bear"
        },
        {
            "start": 514.66,
            "end": 516.4,
            "text": " or run from the bear."
        },
        {
            "start": 516.42,
            "end": 518.84,
            "text": " And that is wonderful."
        },
        {
            "start": 518.86,
            "end": 522.2800000000001,
            "text": " If you're in a forest, and there's a bear."
        },
        {
            "start": 522.3000000000001,
            "end": 530.1,
            "text": " But the problem is what happens when the bear comes home every night,"
        },
        {
            "start": 530.12,
            "end": 536.02,
            "text": " and this system is activated over and over and over again."
        },
        {
            "start": 536.0400000000001,
            "end": 540.38,
            "text": " And it goes from being adaptive or life-saving"
        },
        {
            "start": 540.4,
            "end": 544.24,
            "text": " to maladaptive or health-damaging."
        },
        {
            "start": 544.26,
            "end": 549.94,
            "text": " Children are especially sensitive to this repeated stress activation"
        },
        {
            "start": 549.96,
            "end": 553.74,
            "text": " because their brains and bodies are just developing."
        },
        {
            "start": 553.76,
            "end": 559.82,
            "text": " High doses of adversity not only affect brain structure and function,"
        },
        {
            "start": 559.84,
            "end": 563.42,
            "text": " they affect the developing immune system,"
        },
        {
            "start": 563.44,
            "end": 565.86,
            "text": " developing hormonal systems,"
        },
        {
            "start": 565.88,
            "end": 570.94,
            "text": " and even the way our DNA is read and transcribed."
        },
        {
            "start": 571.94,
            "end": 576.62,
            "text": " So for me, this information threw my old training out the window"
        },
        {
            "start": 576.6400000000001,
            "end": 580.3800000000001,
            "text": " because when we understand the mechanism of a disease,"
        },
        {
            "start": 580.4000000000001,
            "end": 583.7600000000001,
            "text": " when we know not only which pathways are disrupted,"
        },
        {
            "start": 583.7800000000001,
            "end": 587.1800000000001,
            "text": " but how, then as doctors,"
        },
        {
            "start": 587.2,
            "end": 592.6800000000001,
            "text": " it is our job to use this science for prevention and treatment."
        },
        {
            "start": 592.7,
            "end": 594.5600000000001,
            "text": " That's what we do."
        },
        {
            "start": 594.58,
            "end": 598.36,
            "text": " So in San Francisco, we created the Center for Youth Wellness"
        },
        {
            "start": 598.52,
            "end": 603.82,
            "text": " to prevent, screen and heal the impacts of ACEs and toxic stress."
        },
        {
            "start": 604.62,
            "end": 608.66,
            "text": " We started simply with routine screening of every one of our kids"
        },
        {
            "start": 608.6800000000001,
            "end": 610.26,
            "text": " at their regular physical,"
        },
        {
            "start": 610.28,
            "end": 614.9,
            "text": " because I know that if my patient has an ACE score of four,"
        },
        {
            "start": 614.92,
            "end": 619.6,
            "text": " she's two and a half times as likely to develop hepatitis or COPD."
        },
        {
            "start": 619.62,
            "end": 622.46,
            "text": " She's four and a half times as likely to become depressed,"
        },
        {
            "start": 622.48,
            "end": 626.66,
            "text": " and she's 12 times as likely to attempt to take her own life"
        },
        {
            "start": 626.7199999999999,
            "end": 628.64,
            "text": " as my patient with zero ACEs."
        },
        {
            "start": 628.66,
            "end": 632.04,
            "text": " I know that when she's in my exam room."
        },
        {
            "start": 632.06,
            "end": 634.6999999999999,
            "text": " For our patients who do screen positive,"
        },
        {
            "start": 634.7199999999999,
            "end": 637.38,
            "text": " we have a multidisciplinary treatment team"
        },
        {
            "start": 637.4,
            "end": 640.42,
            "text": " that works to reduce the dose of adversity"
        },
        {
            "start": 640.4399999999999,
            "end": 643.0799999999999,
            "text": " and treat symptoms using best practices,"
        },
        {
            "start": 643.1,
            "end": 644.9,
            "text": " including home visits,"
        },
        {
            "start": 644.92,
            "end": 649.5,
            "text": " care coordination, mental health care, nutrition,"
        },
        {
            "start": 649.52,
            "end": 651.4,
            "text": " holistic interventions,"
        },
        {
            "start": 651.42,
            "end": 654.48,
            "text": " and, yes, medication when necessary."
        },
        {
            "start": 654.54,
            "end": 656.96,
            "text": " But we also educate parents"
        },
        {
            "start": 656.98,
            "end": 659.5600000000001,
            "text": " about the impact of ACEs and toxic stress"
        },
        {
            "start": 659.58,
            "end": 663.16,
            "text": " the same way you would for covering electrical outlets"
        },
        {
            "start": 663.1800000000001,
            "end": 664.86,
            "text": " or lead poisoning."
        },
        {
            "start": 664.88,
            "end": 668.76,
            "text": " And we tailor the care of our asthmatics and our diabetics"
        },
        {
            "start": 668.78,
            "end": 670.72,
            "text": " in a way that recognizes"
        },
        {
            "start": 670.74,
            "end": 673.22,
            "text": " that they may need more aggressive treatment"
        },
        {
            "start": 673.24,
            "end": 677.0,
            "text": " given the changes to their hormonal and immune systems."
        },
        {
            "start": 677.98,
            "end": 681.82,
            "text": " So the other thing that happens when you understand this science"
        },
        {
            "start": 681.84,
            "end": 684.6,
            "text": " is that you want to shout it from the rooftops,"
        },
        {
            "start": 684.62,
            "end": 688.5200000000001,
            "text": " because this isn't just an issue for kids in Bayview."
        },
        {
            "start": 689.3000000000001,
            "end": 692.38,
            "text": " I figured the minute that everybody else heard about this,"
        },
        {
            "start": 692.4000000000001,
            "end": 696.0400000000001,
            "text": " it would be routine screening, multidisciplinary treatment teams,"
        },
        {
            "start": 696.0600000000001,
            "end": 697.8000000000001,
            "text": " and it would be a race"
        },
        {
            "start": 697.82,
            "end": 700.4000000000001,
            "text": " to the most effective clinical treatment protocols."
        },
        {
            "start": 701.4200000000001,
            "end": 703.4000000000001,
            "text": " Yeah, that did not happen."
        },
        {
            "start": 703.4200000000001,
            "end": 707.8000000000001,
            "text": " And that was a huge learning for me."
        },
        {
            "start": 707.82,
            "end": 712.32,
            "text": " What I had thought of as simply best clinical practice,"
        },
        {
            "start": 712.34,
            "end": 716.2600000000001,
            "text": " I now understand to be a movement."
        },
        {
            "start": 717.22,
            "end": 719.2800000000001,
            "text": " In the words of Dr. Robert Block,"
        },
        {
            "start": 719.3000000000001,
            "end": 723.3800000000001,
            "text": " the former president of the American Academy of Pediatrics,"
        },
        {
            "start": 723.4000000000001,
            "end": 726.0000000000001,
            "text": " adverse childhood experiences"
        },
        {
            "start": 726.0200000000001,
            "end": 730.96,
            "text": " are the single greatest unaddressed public health threat"
        },
        {
            "start": 730.98,
            "end": 732.84,
            "text": " facing our nation today."
        },
        {
            "start": 733.6,
            "end": 735.3000000000001,
            "text": " And for a lot of people,"
        },
        {
            "start": 735.32,
            "end": 737.7400000000001,
            "text": " that's a terrifying prospect."
        },
        {
            "start": 737.76,
            "end": 741.96,
            "text": " The scope and scale of the problem seems so large"
        },
        {
            "start": 741.98,
            "end": 746.12,
            "text": " that it feels overwhelming to think about how we might approach it."
        },
        {
            "start": 746.14,
            "end": 750.86,
            "text": " But for me, that's actually where the hope lies."
        },
        {
            "start": 750.88,
            "end": 753.48,
            "text": " Because when we have the right framework,"
        },
        {
            "start": 753.5,
            "end": 758.84,
            "text": " when we recognize this to be a public health crisis,"
        },
        {
            "start": 758.86,
            "end": 761.88,
            "text": " then we can begin to use the right toolkit"
        },
        {
            "start": 761.9,
            "end": 763.92,
            "text": " to come up with solutions."
        },
        {
            "start": 763.94,
            "end": 767.52,
            "text": " From tobacco, to lead poisoning, to HIV AIDS,"
        },
        {
            "start": 767.54,
            "end": 772.26,
            "text": " the United States actually has quite a strong track record"
        },
        {
            "start": 772.28,
            "end": 775.66,
            "text": " with addressing public health problems."
        },
        {
            "start": 775.68,
            "end": 778.34,
            "text": " But replicating those successes"
        },
        {
            "start": 778.36,
            "end": 781.0799999999999,
            "text": " with ACEs and toxic stress"
        },
        {
            "start": 781.1,
            "end": 785.38,
            "text": " is going to take determination and commitment."
        },
        {
            "start": 785.4,
            "end": 789.74,
            "text": " And when I look at what our nation's response has been so far,"
        },
        {
            "start": 789.76,
            "end": 792.06,
            "text": " I wonder,"
        },
        {
            "start": 792.0799999999999,
            "end": 795.0799999999999,
            "text": " why haven't we taken this more seriously?"
        },
        {
            "start": 795.1,
            "end": 796.6999999999999,
            "text": " You know, at first,"
        },
        {
            "start": 796.76,
            "end": 798.96,
            "text": " I thought that we marginalize the issue"
        },
        {
            "start": 798.98,
            "end": 801.2,
            "text": " because it doesn't apply to us, right?"
        },
        {
            "start": 801.22,
            "end": 804.1,
            "text": " That's an issue for those kids in those neighborhoods,"
        },
        {
            "start": 804.12,
            "end": 807.4000000000001,
            "text": " which is weird because the data doesn't bear that out."
        },
        {
            "start": 808.5200000000001,
            "end": 812.34,
            "text": " The original ACE study was done in a population"
        },
        {
            "start": 812.36,
            "end": 814.96,
            "text": " that was 70 percent Caucasian,"
        },
        {
            "start": 814.98,
            "end": 817.0600000000001,
            "text": " 70 percent college-educated."
        },
        {
            "start": 818.08,
            "end": 822.38,
            "text": " But then, the more I talk to folks,"
        },
        {
            "start": 822.4000000000001,
            "end": 825.9000000000001,
            "text": " I'm beginning to think that maybe I had it completely backwards."
        },
        {
            "start": 827.2800000000001,
            "end": 832.22,
            "text": " If I were to ask how many people in this room"
        },
        {
            "start": 832.24,
            "end": 837.6,
            "text": " grew up with a family member who suffered from mental illness,"
        },
        {
            "start": 837.62,
            "end": 840.1800000000001,
            "text": " I bet a few hands would go up."
        },
        {
            "start": 840.2,
            "end": 844.0400000000001,
            "text": " And then if I were to ask how many folks had a parent"
        },
        {
            "start": 844.0600000000001,
            "end": 845.72,
            "text": " who maybe drank too much"
        },
        {
            "start": 845.74,
            "end": 851.22,
            "text": " or who really believed that if you spare the rod, you spoiled the child,"
        },
        {
            "start": 851.24,
            "end": 853.32,
            "text": " I bet a few more hands would go up."
        },
        {
            "start": 854.5,
            "end": 856.5600000000001,
            "text": " Even in this room,"
        },
        {
            "start": 856.58,
            "end": 859.12,
            "text": " this is an issue that touches many of us."
        },
        {
            "start": 859.1400000000001,
            "end": 861.1,
            "text": " And I'm beginning to believe"
        },
        {
            "start": 861.12,
            "end": 865.4000000000001,
            "text": " that we marginalize the issue because it does apply to us."
        },
        {
            "start": 865.4200000000001,
            "end": 868.1,
            "text": " Maybe it's easier to see in other zip codes"
        },
        {
            "start": 868.12,
            "end": 870.0400000000001,
            "text": " because we don't want to look at it."
        },
        {
            "start": 870.7800000000001,
            "end": 872.3000000000001,
            "text": " We'd rather be sick."
        },
        {
            "start": 873.82,
            "end": 880.98,
            "text": " Fortunately, scientific advances and, frankly, economic realities"
        },
        {
            "start": 881.0000000000001,
            "end": 884.46,
            "text": " make that option less viable every day."
        },
        {
            "start": 885.46,
            "end": 887.0,
            "text": " The science is clear."
        },
        {
            "start": 887.9000000000001,
            "end": 892.6800000000001,
            "text": " Early adversity dramatically affects health across the lifetime."
        },
        {
            "start": 893.82,
            "end": 896.6,
            "text": " Today, we are beginning to understand"
        },
        {
            "start": 896.62,
            "end": 900.1800000000001,
            "text": " how to interrupt the progression from early adversity"
        },
        {
            "start": 900.2,
            "end": 902.2,
            "text": " to disease and early death."
        },
        {
            "start": 902.86,
            "end": 905.22,
            "text": " And 30 years from now,"
        },
        {
            "start": 905.24,
            "end": 907.6600000000001,
            "text": " the child who has a high ACE score"
        },
        {
            "start": 907.6800000000001,
            "end": 911.1,
            "text": " and whose behavioral symptoms go unrecognized,"
        },
        {
            "start": 911.12,
            "end": 913.98,
            "text": " whose asthma management is not connected"
        },
        {
            "start": 914.04,
            "end": 916.86,
            "text": " and who goes on to develop high blood pressure"
        },
        {
            "start": 916.88,
            "end": 919.88,
            "text": " and early heart disease or cancer"
        },
        {
            "start": 919.9,
            "end": 924.9,
            "text": " will be just as anomalous as a six-month mortality from HIV-AIDS."
        },
        {
            "start": 924.9200000000001,
            "end": 927.28,
            "text": " People will look at that situation and say,"
        },
        {
            "start": 927.3000000000001,
            "end": 929.0,
            "text": " what the heck happened there?"
        },
        {
            "start": 930.4,
            "end": 932.4,
            "text": " This is treatable."
        },
        {
            "start": 932.4200000000001,
            "end": 934.4200000000001,
            "text": " This is beatable."
        },
        {
            "start": 935.28,
            "end": 939.46,
            "text": " The single most important thing that we need today"
        },
        {
            "start": 939.48,
            "end": 943.12,
            "text": " is the courage to look this problem in the face"
        },
        {
            "start": 943.14,
            "end": 947.24,
            "text": " and say, this is real, and this is all of us."
        },
        {
            "start": 948.18,
            "end": 952.12,
            "text": " I believe that we are the movement."
        },
        {
            "start": 953.0600000000001,
            "end": 954.0600000000001,
            "text": " Thank you."
        },
        {
            "start": 954.0600000000001,
            "end": 955.12,
            "text": " Thank you."
        }
    ]
}